Advanced Lane Finding Project¶

The goals / steps of this project are the following:

  • Compute the camera calibration matrix and distortion coefficients given a set of chessboard images.
  • Apply a distortion correction to raw images.
  • Use color transforms, gradients, etc., to create a thresholded binary image.
  • Apply a perspective transform to rectify binary image ("birds-eye view").
  • Detect lane pixels and fit to find the lane boundary.
  • Determine the curvature of the lane and vehicle position with respect to center.
  • Warp the detected lane boundaries back onto the original image.
  • Output visual display of the lane boundaries and numerical estimation of lane curvature and vehicle position.

First, I'll compute the camera calibration using chessboard images¶

from lib.utils import get_perspective_transform_meta_data


img_size_x = img.shape[1]
img_size_y = img.shape[0]
img_size = (img_size_x, img_size_y)
src, dst, transform_matrix, transform_inv_matrix = get_perspective_transform_meta_data(img_size_x, img_size_y)

Step 4. Identify lane-line pixels and fit their positions with a polynomial¶

In [8]:
from lib.find_line_poly import search_poly_from_scratch, search_poly_around_old, visualize_poly
%matplotlib inline
bindary_transformed = cv2.warpPerspective(bindary_img, transform_matrix, img_size)
_, _, left_fit, right_fit, ploty, out_img = search_poly_from_scratch(bindary_transformed, draw_out_img=True)

left_fitx = left_fit[0] * ploty ** 2 + left_fit[1] * ploty + left_fit[2]
cv2.polylines(out_img, np.int_(np.dstack((left_fitx, ploty))), False, color=(255, 255, 0), thickness=8)

right_fitx = right_fit[0] * ploty ** 2 + right_fit[1] * ploty + right_fit[2]
cv2.polylines(out_img, np.int_(np.dstack((right_fitx, ploty))), False, color=(255, 255, 0), thickness=8)

search_poly_from_img = out_img

plt.imshow(search_poly_from_img)
plt.imsave('output_images/search_poly_from_img.jpg', search_poly_from_img)
